'That was really upsetting. It was really disgusting - not something that I would want to see.'

'I was left nervous, thinking about what he might do in the future... I was worried that he was mentally unstable,' Miss Marsh added.

She told the court she had initially asked police not to take any action in case it encouraged Mafwenke to escalate his stalking campaign.

