Asked by the Crown what she feared could happen, Miss Marsh said: 'I thought it might be rape, murder, kidnap. In my line of work, you don’t think anything is too far-fetched.'

The frequency of the letters then increased to up to five per week with the mail being sent by recorded delivery.

One letter said: 'I love you and the way you are alone... I plan to have four babies with you in married life. Thank you for I make it happen.'

'Our time is now to have our childrens,' another read.

